flavourText: <size:25>{"Glimmers of benevolence,
Shrouded a lacquered lust for power,
Yet still they followed his influence."}
<size:31>{The end of the old,
the beginning of the new.
A unique opportunity for transformation,
for those with the power
to grasp it.}
Exploring lands made of flesh and sorrow, we'll reap and plunder like there's no tomorrow.
<size:28>{Through the eyes of a person,
you can see their soul
Through the eyes of a jewel,
you can see the universe}
In the dead of night you may elude your shadows,
but they will always find you by dawn.
<size:25>{Summoned for the King's desire,
soon applause came from the court.
However insanity was his only sire,
so the King's reign was cut short.}
"The Karui was correct; there is virtue in honouring my ancestors."
Beware the combatant who shows no confidence, yet still enters the ring, for they are surely hiding something.
The Mists of Madness prey on those who harbour the deepest of fears.
Life isn't what you make of it, it's already been made for you.
"Don't worry, I know what I'm doing."
- Toggo's Last Words
<smaller>{They fought the storm together as one,
Until the longest of days was done.
Their love grew stronger
with every breath,
Until it was broken apart in death.}

<size:26>{"I wanted to give you three things. I've given you my eternal love. I've sung to you my most beautiful song. I'd have given you the moon last, but it couldn't be found. I hope you'll accept this instead."}
Dost thou lead my men to victory, my child?
"When grasped in his hand, even an ordinary piece of wood can make the heavens tremble with fear."
No matter where your dreams take you, Nightmare follows close behind.
A beacon on the horizon; a guiding light, a call for help, or a warning to turn back.
When there is no other choice, even the meekest whisper can bring about the greatest storm.
Their whims left unknown,
Their life left for others.
The strongest emerge from suffering. The toughest bear the most scars. The sole survivor claims the greatest of rewards.
Though they were a pack of elite combatants, the Emperor's royal guards were not ready to face one of his notorious parties.
"In the forest again... But at least I have these."
<size:31>{It's always easier to find your way if you draw a map of the progress you've made.}
"Only after one forsakes rage, can true power be found."
- Sekhema Asenath
<size:28>{Scaly beast of the skies,
watching with his golden eyes.
Shadow that blocks out the sun,
it's too late for you to run.}
An oath once made is an oath never broken. Do not delay in keeping it, for I take no pleasure in fools.
For every threat you spy in the shadows, there are two others you don't.
Our Lady Dialla,
as a symbol of our progress,
shines greater than all the gems.
A map is only useful if you know where you stand.
<size:31>{As their civilisation crumbled, the Vaal looked to their queen. In her, they saw a way out. In them, she saw a burden she was happy to free herself from.}
Sometimes your greatest enemy is the only one keeping you breathing.
"This one? It is NOT for sale. You would sooner pry it from my lifeless hand."
- Jonfé Darontos, Ringmaker
<size:29>{The largest beasts cannot be overpowered. The Greatwolf teaches us to use guile, not strength, to probe for the soft flesh and strike deep.}
Though the years weakened his mind, his body remained deadly as ever.
The world is ever-changing.
Once-lush woods now lost beneath shifting sands,
Great cities now drown beneath turbulent waters.
Adapt or perish.
Try a thousand times, and eventually you'll have to give up.
<size:28>{We live to dream of worlds we aren't in,
a false narrative that we use to fill our souls
with doubt;
The world is already beautiful,
there's no need to dream.}
Genius knows no limits.
A boy who grows up with everything learns to appreciate nothing.
They said they were here to protect us.
To protect her mansion, she would cut a deal with anyone. Anything.
Something answered.
Unlimited power is apt to corrupt the minds of those who possess it.
Oh the places you will go, the sights you will see, the things you will meet.
<size:30>{A King Loved By All,
A Shadow Awaiting Nightfall,
A Speaker Howling Away,
A Hunter Seeking Prey}
It's sad times we live in when a friendship has a price people are willing to pay.
"Masters of wit, strength and cunning. To survive the harsh winters, you must be like the fox."
- Ezomyte Proverb
Warriors of a distant land, you embark on a journey from which you may not return, but which we will be all the better for.
The First Ones
may be blasphemy,
but they are
powerful blasphemy.
They whose lives were given to clothe the Dark Dreamer... They were the lucky ones.
They say it is the head that leads, but all must flow through the body at some point.
<size:28>{A symbol of beauty and innocence
The gems corrupted her mind
Malachai corrupted her gems
All but a glimmer of
greatness lost in madness}
"No man can best me, no demon can fell me. For I vanquish all with my axe!"
<size:27>{"There are worlds that lie beyond the edge of my page, the edge of my understanding. Worlds of wonder. Worlds of terror."
Aramil - Cartographer to Emperor Chitus}
"There is no right or wrong choice, no best or worst. There are only choices and their consequences."
All dreams vanish when the dreamers wake.
The house always wins.
<size:30>{"Let us not forget the most important lesson the Vaal taught us:
Nothing is eternal."
- Siosa Foaga, Imperial Scholar}
To her beauty you submit,
lest your neck the great Queen slit.
Turn the crank,
close your eyes,
and pray to the gods
for a pleasant surprise.
<size:28>{"The Seas Call, the Mad Answer"}
<size:33>{Weaving through the cracks, searching for weaknesses, silent, indiscriminate, leaving sorrow in its wake.}
On the 21st of Eterni,
two become one,
their light outshines
the setting sun.
"Our rulers are being ridiculous, and we are suffering."
In the hands of a master craftsman, a worthless pebble can adorn the crown of a king.
"There are two ways to pay, Gold and Blood. I'll take my share in both."
-Cameria the Coldblooded
The jeweller's true talent is the capacity to see a jewel's beauty before they draw it out.
<size:31>{Sometimes an apprentice becomes a master through countless hours of hard work and practice.
Sometimes it happens by force.}
He shattered Her smile
Scattered the fragments like ash
All she did was laugh
<size:28>{I gave my mind without a fight,
The twelfth hour I lost control.
The day is gone but there is light,
eyes that glow like red-hot coal.}
"He might be lacking in vision, but his virtuosity is undeniable."
- Malachai, on Maligaro
Necromancers, believe me, are more terrifying than their thralls.
Taste and grow strong. Drink too much and be buried.
The village elders had a curious rule: If you hear three voices scream for aid, flee as fast as you can.
"Sometimes, the most beautiful treasures...are the ones you cannot have."
- Beryl, Survivor from the Azurite Mines
"Some see our mortal flesh as a limitation. I see it as an opportunity for vast, miraculous improvements."
- Shavronne of Umbra
Claw them from the bottom, you'll be glad that you have got 'em, claw them from the top, you'll never want to stop.
Only the feminine touch can save a man's soul from the clutches of The Wasteland.
Formless might,
Wild beauty tamed,
The brine of gods,
The seas restrained.
Bound by fate,
inseparable by choice.
You can change your name, but you cannot change your history.
Mold the world with your bare hands. Be careful, for what is your doing might become your undoing.
Ever get the feeling you're being watched...?
<size:31>{The others succumbed to madness and depravity, but Lori fought on. Alone in the darkness, she could still see the dull light of hope's distant dawn.}
When the dead raise and master their own, the land is truly lost.
The howls and cackling could not mask the sadness.
To own a piece of the Nightmare, you must first belong to the Nightmare.
To know the monster, you must become the monster.
"Only a fool looks to the occult for power and expects to be spared from its wrath."
- Voll, Emperor of Purity
Lethal, untouchable, keen, aflame. Just what I was looking for.
"I don't believe in karma. If it were real, I would never win."
"Fear controls the masses."
- Laszlo, the Scourge
They came from far and wide under a common banner.
They sought companionship and competition,
but found a treasure none had foreseen.
Fear the man who lusts for power, for he will do anything to get it.
<size:28>{First, I gave my wealth, and we went hungry. Next, I gave my land, and we were homeless. Then, I gave my family, and I was alone. Last, I gave my eyes, and all I could dream was mine.}
<size:29>{A mind as quick as lightning,
fists as hard as stone,
a heart that burns with fury,
and eyes that chill to the bone.}
Wrapped in the glory of the heavens, she comes to mete out justice for the fallen.
<size:32>{Blood flows not just through veins, but through worlds.}
<size:31>{500 times Kaom's axe fell, 500 times Kaom's Heart splintered. Finally, all that remained was a terrible, heartless Fury.}
The path to godhood is guided by the hand of sacrifice.
<size:27>{God had forsaken the land
And Victario wept.
Corruption consumed the land
And Victario's tears turned to blood.}
<size:31>{"Daughter of catastrophe, mother of pain. Amongst the filth of Wraeclast, she wanders, and her wrath follows." - Quintoon the Returned}
One who is blinded by their past may only see a sliver of the present.
<size:31>{The Eternals lauded his valour. The Karui relished his defeat. Yet the final thoughts of Marceus Lioneye were naught but lament for his pride.}
No blade subdues vice;
Guide offenders to virtue,
Unveil their lost sight.
Before gemlings, before thaumaturgy, a simple court magician could enthrall the masses.
<size:30>{A weapon, a shelter, a prison.
The web's purpose changes
with the spider's needs.
A lesson we should
take to heart.}
"I'm going for a walk. I'll be back soon."
- Blonca's last words
In combat, a warrior must first be resourceful,
and second, decisive.
<size:26>{The strange voice showed Aul a future where his legacy was forgotten, where new cultures broke themselves upon Aul's ruined world.}
The first quill separates the quick learners from the dead.
Become the leader you were born to be.
Lucian lost himself in ancient scrolls and found in those scrolls a love whose power bridged a millennium.
You gave us life and love, more than you could spare. Now you're gone, and we are stranded, alone, cold and without purpose.
The suit I wear,
Is heavy and bare.
A canvas, it seems, breathing life into dreams.
<size:31>{There is no mistake so great that it cannot be undone.}
If you look hard enough for hidden meaning, you will find it.
From death, life.
From life, death.
The wheel turns,
and the corbies wheel overhead.
<size:28>{"You cannot portray the world using just one colour. Together, you and I, we will paint our world into perfection."
- Kyra, renegade thaumaturgist}

flavourText: Without the ability to weep, the heart hardens against both the pure and the corrupt.
<size:30>{"Long ago, people looked to the stars, believing they influenced us. Soon, it will be us who influence the stars."
- Doryani, Queen's Thaumaturge}
Chaos spread, wreaking havoc and death. They said none would be spared, and yet here I stand.
The harvest ended, the floods began.
"Hold your tongue before I claim it." - Doedre Darktongue
Accumulating wealth has its own costs.
I've never come upon a ship I could not command. I have however met sailors that were not willing to be led.

<size:25>{"To know for what you fight. To get up again when you've been struck down. To outmanoeuvre someone faster, trick someone smarter, crush someone stronger. That's what it takes to claim the crown."
- Daresso, the King of Swords}
Those whose hands are their livelihood know the importance of keeping them safe and warm.
Method transcends shape and size. Do something in parallel long enough, and you will always find
another way.
<size:28>{Wreathed in the skin and bones
of the beasts she slew,
her gift came from what she lost:
her humanity.}
Two sides of a coin;
Heads for a friend,
tails a foe;
Gemini toss up
True to his title,
Voll, newly crowned,
had many of the
Eternal Empire's signature
extravagances destroyed.
<size:31>{Brutus' first innovation as Lord Incarcerator was a weighted chain around every neck so that his prisoners would forever bow to him.}
Greed is a hunger that only grows as you feed it
However vicious Rhoas might be, a dedicated angler may in time tame them.
Let these fine arrows pack a punch.
Rigwald believed he'd seized great power, but it was the great power that had seized Rigwald
Some gifts are obligations while others are simply opportunities.
Perfection is the standard, excellence will be handled on a case by case basis.
Even the most learned man is a fool to his own fate.
You cannot journey to new lands until you have the courage to leave the safety of home.
To cure the Goddess,
and break the chains of corruption,
you must shatter the world.
"Through thick and thin,
blood and bone,
a peaceful life
is one I can't condone."
- Tukohama, Father Of War
<size:27>{Thy knee shall bend
in shifting dark,
thy blade shall serve his vigil.
Thy oath shall bind thee
to his mark,
thy flesh shall bear his sigil.}
Loyalty can be bought. Just make sure you know who the buyer is.
The academic route to knowledge is wide and well-trodden; but it is the untaught one who scales the mountain.
<size:29>{"Fate was always my nemesis...
But it didn't stop me then, and it won't stop me now."
- Kjetilbrann, The Undaunted}
The day is dying, the night is born, the air grows cool, the sky is torn.
'Lightning never strikes the same place twice'
is really just wishful thinking.
<size:31>{Strange eyes on top of spines
Gaze beyond the veil of time
Deep down below the mines
A dream of crimson and of grime}
<size:29>{A dark note drips
from the dreamer's lips,
A honeyed melody.
We stand, we fall
on his beck and call,
for in his dream we're free.}
<size:27>{The mighty warriors traded in blows, the nimble archers in arrows, yet it was the brazen thaumaturgists who would bring catastrophe to all.}
A life lost, A legacy born.
They stand among us, and within us.
Some seek to change the world. Others change the world as a consequence of what they seek.
Nature was her domain,
Love was her song,
Family was her devotion,
Knowledge was her gift.
Every obsession began with a single, innocent taste.
Trying to bring your vision to life is enough to drive you mad.
"The house always wins... except when I do."
<size:24>{Dread and danger
makes the air feel thin.
Above, power slumbers, tempting fate.
Greed and ambition
draws countless in,
For those who seek power
can never wait.}
Scarier than any criminal is an innocent man in chains, for when he breaks free, his revenge will be justified.
"I gave up my body for you. I gave up my name for you. And one day I shall give up my life for you."
<size:27>{A wanderer in the wild strives
Against countless foes he survives
A fool pursues a quest contrived
By the gift of the witch, alive.}
The Poet's blood is the Empire's ink.
Jump right in,
But beware
Of things broken
Or beyond compare.
"On this day I mark the first of many agreements that I will have with this land and its people."
<size:24>{For the blessed bear in the cave,
A hundred days pass in silence and darkness,
until moon begins its fourth passage,
the bear sheds her beastly fur,
and is reborn, human and whole.}
A good spy doesn't forget she's gone undercover.
Reach into the Void and claim your prize.
The Ezomyte, desperate for aid, cried out to the gods.
<size:28>{You can't seek riches without getting your hands dirty.}
<size:28>{Charmed by beautiful stones
Consumed with the
pursuit of perfection
Ever deeper into the waiting dark}
The dead tell me great insights. They've had nothing but time to sit and think.
<size:34>{He dispels dark realms
until mortal sufferings
yield to hopeful light.}
There are countless worlds, but only those with limitless potential will be able to achieve perfection.
In the pursuit of wealth, as in that of power, anything goes.
A tower built of the strongest stone is not eternal; a towering intellect is not enlightened.
It is with the smallest of words that we find the largest of truths.
Some powers are far too great even for the
gods of old.
<size:29>{Moribund, he gazed upon the journey taken as blood trickled down his chin. His eye closed on the city ahead that he would never call home.}
Shame what happened to my husband. He had such good taste.
The hermit's only friend is the greenery he can find.
Wealth can, in fact, buy happiness.
We play at God with our necromancy,
but forces far more potent
sleep within these stones.
<size:28>{A map is similar
to a pair of eyes,
without one you stumble
around, unable to find your way.}
"Set your life on fire. Seek those who fan your flames"
-Rumi of the Vaal
Maligaro may have valued function over form, but that did not mute his flair for the dramatic.
A dream from which you cannot awake is nothing other than a nightmare.
Though the path to divinity is fraught with peril, hope may bloom from within.
Take small pieces of things and then assemble them together
Never dying, yet not living,
Endlessly they wander
beneath the harvest moon.
<size:28>{I never truly understood the depths of my insanity,
until I realized the voices beckoning me towards the abyss,
were none other than my own.}
<size:28>{The hatungo know many answers to the same question,
for time itself is a tangled web.}
<size:29>{Three men travel
through the gate;
they carry a protective ward.
A faction conspires
against their fate,
but magic unravels the sword.}
Time cannot wash away that which cannot be forgotten.
Eternal beauty has a cost, one which Shavronne was happy to pay with the lives of others.
No man may hope to turn back the storm. You can only hope you do not attract its ire.
A taste of power brings a hunger for more.
Primed, curved and sleek.
Decisive and final.
For malice and righteousness.
There's but one solution.
In the prison of all sins, will you grasp godhood or sorrow? Only hope lies under the shadows.
Whoever said 'more is always better' has obviously never met a rat.
<size:28>{A ravenous mind can readily take in ideas from any source.
Fortunately for the scholars, he has already learned about sustainability.}
<size:23>{Vintage or crafted, Glittering and shiny
Dusty or glittering, huge or tiny
Secured within a chest
or unearthed from your mining
Find jewellery everywhere,
no need for divining!
So why is it so hard
to figure out which one to wear?
This one makes me stronger,
but does it match my hair?}
Our world, dangerous as it is, is far safer than what lies just beyond our sight.
When the outcome is the same, does it matter if it is fortune or trickery?
<size:26>{Black and White, Silver and Gold
Let us see the world Unfold
Red and Blue, Yellow and Green
Let us remake it in colours Unseen}
No one ever truly understood what she meant when she said she wanted to raise a family.
<size:29>{"I swore to use my position to help the people. What good is power when it just accumulates on the already-powerful?" - Erasmus, Imperial Gemcutter}
They say when a dragon dies, the flesh smoulders and burns until all that remains is the still, white-hot, heart.
"Experiment 22A: Rhoas, when deprived of water, secrete a most delightfully potent toxin."
- Maligaro
Upon seeing her face, I am terrified—the moon shows me my own form!
<size:26>{Many were slain by the sword king
Their blood decorating his ring
Those who retreated were slaughtered
Those who fought bravely were honoured}
<size:30>{Many strive for greatness,
but it is challenge, unforseen,
that forges heroes.}
The fight is the easy part. It's the years of training that'll kill you.
"Man may shape the world, but these? These shape the man." -Inquisitor Maligaro
As countless fractures weaken the divide, nightmares seep through from the other side.
The thumb turns down
and the crowd roars,
they want death
and the blood is yours.
"If I fall, we will fall together with my fangs in your throat."
Justice comes swift
Equal to the crime
Revenge is a gift
Life for a life
Eye for an eye
<size:26>{Embrace death to honour the lost,
no fear in life no matter the cost.
With one of all we are,
and all of one we trust,
throughout past, present and future... be just.}
<size:26>{The rain pelts down, Mud grasping at his feet, as thoughts of those in his care bolster his resolve.}
The earth offers nourishment, growth and healing. Unless, of course, the sky has other plans.
Time and change
shall naught avail,
To dim the Light
of Truth's fair grail.
<size:31>{Born of relentless fury and abhorrence, warped by turmoil and anguish, tainted through desire and carnality, I thirst for bloodshed once more.}
"Many believe murder is a grisly, grim, and grotesque crime. Then there are those who simply make art of it."
You'll never know the things you miss if you keep your eyes closed
Boundless is the distance between where we start and where we start again.
"Bino's brief career as a chef at Axiom saved the executioner a lot of work."
So many memories,
so much pain in
such a small token.
Drown it in blood
so you can forget.
Fall into endless night; a voyage into an ocean of oblivion.
Luck is a fool's game, and I know plenty of rich fools.
<size:28>{Crimson rubies, drops of vigour,
flowing through my veins,
flesh like coal, try to crush me,
diamond is what remains.}
The mind had much to endure before the advent of thaumaturgy.
"More! I want more!" - Faendris, the Insatiable
Some things should not be used. Some power is too great a risk.
While the Labyrinth traps have claimed countless adventurers, they were not designed with felines in mind.
I have a headache, can anyone find me a nurse?
Time dismantles all things eventually, but some wish to accelerate the process.
The most pathetic person in the world is someone who has sight, but no vision.
Beware the sudden calm, for it is a sure sign of a storm on the horizon.
<size:31>{A month's work, a year's wages, a foolish shortcut through a Rhoa's nest, and a grieving bride-to-be, who never received her betrothed's great gift.}
Simple actions can lead the world to an early grave.
If you wish to rush into strange places, be prepared to face strange things.
In a world filled with chaos, he could always seek comfort in the hands of his master.
A lucky number
For us all
To help us through
The perils told.
Lioneye looked to the heights of glorious victory. And thus he missed the defeat right under his nose.
With staff in hand
and wrath in heart,
your soul and corpse
shall surely part.
When you dwell in total darkness, even the faintest light may guide you out.
Sturdy and strong,
grown from the stream.
The Flora that live here,
A combatant's dream.
<size:26>{At the beck and call
of The Siren's hand,
winter ravages
the trembling land,
and the weight of ice that binds
will break the strongest of minds.}
<size:27>{Fire filled the sky that night
Chaos reigned
Where the shards fell
All was destroyed
-Jozen Kasigi, retelling an urban legend of the Cataclysm}
<size:30>{Many that have wielded the power of lightning have said that death by electrocution looks like the victim is more alive than ever before.}
"Oh no, I couldn't possibly afford this fine artefact. I'm... just looking."
<size:25>{They thought winter had come early,
that snow blanketed the land,
but in truth, all their chickens
had come home to roost.}
The line between having not enough to do and too much to do is unusually fine.
Embrace the Light,
Await the Morrow,
No more Spite,
And no more Sorrow.
"Axes and mauls are so uncivilised. A good clean cut to the neck with a sharp blade, that's the Sarn way!"
The finer the brew, the harder it is to remember drinking it.
Be like water, friend.
Discovery can lead to beauty, or it can lead to ruin.
A king's movement is unwavering.
By the time their eyes meet,
the dark deal has long since been made,
and his fate long since sealed.

flavourText: Its body knows no limits. Its appetite knows no bounds.
If this is my dream, I don't wish to wake.
<size:31>{The greatness of a man is not in how much wealth or power he acquires, but in his integrity and his ability to positively affect those around him.}
<size:25>{Seeking shelter from the night,
in the warmth of the run-down inn,
erstwhile foes put aside the fight,
to bond over whiskey and gin.}
<size:31>{Sometimes an apprentice becomes a master through countless hours of hard work and practice.
Sometimes it happens by force.}
Only the feminine touch can save a man's soul from the clutches of The Wasteland.
Those whose hands are their livelihood know the importance of keeping them safe and warm.
On the 21st of Eterni,
two become one,
their light outshines
the setting sun.
<size:28>{"You cannot portray the world using just one colour. Together, you and I, we will paint our world into perfection."
- Kyra, renegade thaumaturgist}
You can change your name, but you cannot change your history.
<size:31>{Born of relentless fury and abhorrence, warped by turmoil and anguish, tainted through desire and carnality, I thirst for bloodshed once more.}
Perfection is the standard, excellence will be handled on a case by case basis.
The finer the brew, the harder it is to remember drinking it.
Scarier than any criminal is an innocent man in chains, for when he breaks free, his revenge will be justified.
<size:31>{The end of the old,
the beginning of the new.
A unique opportunity for transformation,
for those with the power
to grasp it.}
<size:31>{"When Voll spared Malachai, accepting his aid in pursuit of Purity, the strongest faith was infected by Corruption and made brittle as glass."
- Victario, the People's Poet}
Trying to bring your vision to life is enough to drive you mad.
Mold the world with your bare hands. Be careful, for what is your doing might become your undoing.
"Most people only have one. I'm a bit of a hoarder."
<size:24>{Do the simple words used
alone cause men to cheer?
One hundred others might
just as soon make a jeer.
Perchance it was the turn
of the tone in this bit.
See how their hearts shone once,
by my song, they were lit.}
"Set your life on fire. Seek those who fan your flames"
-Rumi of the Vaal
The suit I wear,
Is heavy and bare.
A canvas, it seems, breathing life into dreams.
<size:28>{Wreathed in the skin and bones
of the beasts she slew,
her gift came from what she lost:
her humanity.}
<size:26>{The villain strikes,
the world is torn.
A war begins, a hero is born,
The nemesis sets the sky alight.
A hero's sacrifice
sets everything right.
- Drake's Epitaph}
Where Decay festers, I shall expunge it, and leave in its place a shining monument.
I have a headache, can anyone find me a nurse?
<size:28>{A symbol of beauty and innocence
The gems corrupted her mind
Malachai corrupted her gems
All but a glimmer of
greatness lost in madness}
<size:28>{Through the eyes of a person,
you can see their soul
Through the eyes of a jewel,
you can see the universe}
<size:31>{The Eternals lauded his valour. The Karui relished his defeat. Yet the final thoughts of Marceus Lioneye were naught but lament for his pride.}
"Through thick and thin,
blood and bone,
a peaceful life
is one I can't condone."
- Tukohama, Father Of War
They say when a dragon dies, the flesh smoulders and burns until all that remains is the still, white-hot, heart.
Sometimes you need to make your own luck.
<size:27>{The mighty warriors traded in blows, the nimble archers in arrows, yet it was the brazen thaumaturgists who would bring catastrophe to all.}
Upon seeing her face, I am terrified—the moon shows me my own form!
What was once a passing thought tickling the back of the mind is now a desperate, driving desire.
<size:26>{The rain pelts down, Mud grasping at his feet, as thoughts of those in his care bolster his resolve.}
Take small pieces of things and then assemble them together
"Fear controls the masses."
- Laszlo, the Scourge
Oh the places you will go, the sights you will see, the things you will meet.
To protect her mansion, she would cut a deal with anyone. Anything.
Something answered.
All dreams vanish when the dreamers wake.
Method transcends shape and size. Do something in parallel long enough, and you will always find
another way.
Taste and grow strong. Drink too much and be buried.
The Lord of Chaos dreams as his Eye gazes, unblinking, at his prize. And soon, all shall tremble before his waking form.
Before gemlings, before thaumaturgy, a simple court magician could enthrall the masses.
One who is blinded by their past may only see a sliver of the present.
The Ezomyte, desperate for aid, cried out to the gods.
The jeweller's true talent is the capacity to see a jewel's beauty before they draw it out.
The power of the world,
lies upon your hands.
The mighty huntress always called for her share,
But what we shared was a lifelong bond.
Savour these moments, for they may never return.
"No man can best me, no demon can fell me. For I vanquish all with my axe!"
If you wish to rush into strange places, be prepared to face strange things.
If the path to divinity were simple, we'd all be gods.
The harvest ended, the floods began.
When you strive to write your name on the dense pages of History, someone else, inevitably, must be crossed out.
By the time their eyes meet,
the dark deal has long since been made,
and his fate long since sealed.
In fleeing reality, you step into the realm of madness.
"On this day I mark the first of many agreements that I will have with this land and its people."
<size:24>{Dread and danger
makes the air feel thin.
Above, power slumbers, tempting fate.
Greed and ambition
draws countless in,
For those who seek power
can never wait.}
Shame what happened to my husband. He had such good taste.
The Mists of Madness prey on those who harbour the deepest of fears.
<size:27>{Thy knee shall bend
in shifting dark,
thy blade shall serve his vigil.
Thy oath shall bind thee
to his mark,
thy flesh shall bear his sigil.}
<smaller>{They fought the storm together as one,
Until the longest of days was done.
Their love grew stronger
with every breath,
Until it was broken apart in death.}
When the dead raise and master their own, the land is truly lost.
<size:31>{A month's work, a year's wages, a foolish shortcut through a Rhoa's nest, and a grieving bride-to-be, who never received her betrothed's great gift.}
He shattered Her smile
Scattered the fragments like ash
All she did was laugh

<size:25>{"To know for what you fight. To get up again when you've been struck down. To outmanoeuvre someone faster, trick someone smarter, crush someone stronger. That's what it takes to claim the crown."
- Daresso, the King of Swords}
The thumb turns down
and the crowd roars,
they want death
and the blood is yours.
When the outcome is the same, does it matter if it is fortune or trickery?
"Bino's brief career as a chef at Axiom saved the executioner a lot of work."
"The house always wins... except when I do."
"I don't believe in karma. If it were real, I would never win."
The world is ever-changing.
Once-lush woods now lost beneath shifting sands,
Great cities now drown beneath turbulent waters.
Adapt or perish.
The first quill separates the quick learners from the dead.
His brother would not atone, so he took his brother's life, and with it, his sins.
<size:28>{The hatungo know many answers to the same question,
for time itself is a tangled web.}
All that is flawed is worthless. The slightest error, and this might as well be trash.
For every threat you spy in the shadows, there are two others you don't.
<size:25>{"Glimmers of benevolence,
Shrouded a lacquered lust for power,
Yet still they followed his influence."}
Genius knows no limits.
Sometimes your greatest enemy is the only one keeping you breathing.
<size:27>{A jolt, and it moves. Or smolders.
A current, and it lives. Or dies.
A surge, and it transcends.
Or... not.
Only one way to find out.}
"The most valuable treasures should be hidden in plain sight."
- Ina, Keeper of Goods
Experience teaches us that the cold is not the same as the absence of warmth.
No one ever truly understood what she meant when she said she wanted to raise a family.
You cannot journey to new lands until you have the courage to leave the safety of home.
In the prison of all sins, will you grasp godhood or sorrow? Only hope lies under the shadows.
<size:28>{There's a place where up is down,
where right is wrong,
where pleasure is agony,
and where the living wish only for death.}
In combat, a warrior must first be resourceful,
and second, decisive.
Jump right in,
But beware
Of things broken
Or beyond compare.
They say it is the head that leads, but all must flow through the body at some point.
Know thine enemy better than you know thyself.
"Many believe murder is a grisly, grim, and grotesque crime. Then there are those who simply make art of it."
<size:31>{There is no mistake so great that it cannot be undone.}
Born beneath silver light, bearing Lunaris' mark.
Conjuring all his might, the Prodigy turned light to dark.
"There are two ways to pay, Gold and Blood. I'll take my share in both."
-Cameria the Coldblooded
A life lost, A legacy born.
He appeared before the Light Eater, and at once knew his soul was damned.
The mind had much to endure before the advent of thaumaturgy.
The house always wins.
Time dismantles all things eventually, but some wish to accelerate the process.
Some gifts are obligations while others are simply opportunities.
Fear the man who lusts for power, for he will do anything to get it.
<size:31>{"Mastery of thaumaturgy is like any other pursuit; it requires dedication and sacrifice. Sometimes several sacrifices."
- Shavronne of Umbra}
Necromancers, believe me, are more terrifying than their thralls.
Though the path to divinity is fraught with peril, hope may bloom from within.
Our world, dangerous as it is, is far safer than what lies just beyond our sight.
Lucian lost himself in ancient scrolls and found in those scrolls a love whose power bridged a millennium.
<size:26>{"Such dedication for so many years,
all for a couple extra letters at the front of your name..."}
At night, when the seas are calm, and the skies dark, he can see it. The formless fiend that took his eye, and fractured his mind.
Luck is a fool's game, and I know plenty of rich fools.
Ever get the feeling you're being watched...?
<size:29>{The largest beasts cannot be overpowered. The Greatwolf teaches us to use guile, not strength, to probe for the soft flesh and strike deep.}
The First Ones
may be blasphemy,
but they are
powerful blasphemy.
<size:29>{A dark note drips
from the dreamer's lips,
A honeyed melody.
We stand, we fall
on his beck and call,
for in his dream we're free.}
<size:31>{Each night, the light dies, and each morning she is born anew, embracing the land in her golden wings.}
Claw them from the bottom, you'll be glad that you have got 'em, claw them from the top, you'll never want to stop.
<size:24>{For the blessed bear in the cave,
A hundred days pass in silence and darkness,
until moon begins its fourth passage,
the bear sheds her beastly fur,
and is reborn, human and whole.}
A lucky number
For us all
To help us through
The perils told.
<size:29>{Moribund, he gazed upon the journey taken as blood trickled down his chin. His eye closed on the city ahead that he would never call home.}
"It's risky not knowing where your wares come from. That's why I source my own."
- Klayver, the Antiquarian
True to his title,
Voll, newly crowned,
had many of the
Eternal Empire's signature
extravagances destroyed.
Unlimited power is apt to corrupt the minds of those who possess it.
If time is the most valuable currency, how do you make more of it?
A tower built of the strongest stone is not eternal; a towering intellect is not enlightened.
Gaze towards the stars, but beware what gazes back.
<size:30>{Taste not of their
forbidden fruit.
Theirs is a harvest of
the darkest kind,
twisted, rotten and
damned for eternity.}
Rigwald believed he'd seized great power, but it was the great power that had seized Rigwald
From death, life.
From life, death.
The wheel turns,
and the corbies wheel overhead.
So many memories,
so much pain in
such a small token.
Drown it in blood
so you can forget.
<size:31>{A wolf does not bite his mate as he does his prey, yet both begin with bared teeth. Know who you are, and you will know the meaning of the bite.}
"Some see our mortal flesh as a limitation. I see it as an opportunity for vast, miraculous improvements."
- Shavronne of Umbra
We tried to tell him to get his head checked.
<size:26>{Many were slain by the sword king
Their blood decorating his ring
Those who retreated were slaughtered
Those who fought bravely were honoured}
Boundless is the distance between where we start and where we start again.
No matter where your dreams take you, Nightmare follows close behind.
Justice comes swift
Equal to the crime
Revenge is a gift
Life for a life
Eye for an eye
If you look hard enough for hidden meaning, you will find it.
<size:31>{"Daughter of catastrophe, mother of pain. Amongst the filth of Wraeclast, she wanders, and her wrath follows." - Quintoon the Returned}
Let these fine arrows pack a punch.
In the dead of night you may elude your shadows,
but they will always find you by dawn.
Life isn't what you make of it, it's already been made for you.
For some, the price of power is never too great.
The Poet's blood is the Empire's ink.
<size:33>{Weaving through the cracks, searching for weaknesses, silent, indiscriminate, leaving sorrow in its wake.}

flavourText: Without the ability to weep, the heart hardens against both the pure and the corrupt.
They whose lives were given to clothe the Dark Dreamer... They were the lucky ones.
The fight is the easy part. It's the years of training that'll kill you.
The path to godhood is guided by the hand of sacrifice.
Why settle when more is never enough.
It's sad times we live in when a friendship has a price people are willing to pay.
Some things should not be used. Some power is too great a risk.
It is a mortal man's folly to seek power beyond his comprehension.
Nothing can be heard above the din or seen amongst the turmoil. The senses are shattered. All is left to fate.
In the pursuit of power, as in that of wealth, anything goes.
When you dwell in total darkness, even the faintest light may guide you out.
Loyalty can be bought. Just make sure you know who the buyer is.
<size:30>{"Long ago, people looked to the stars, believing they influenced us. Soon, it will be us who influence the stars."
- Doryani, Queen's Thaumaturge}
Maligaro may have valued function over form, but that did not mute his flair for the dramatic.
Reach into the Void and claim your prize.
"Axes and mauls are so uncivilised. A good clean cut to the neck with a sharp blade, that's the Sarn way!"
Their whims left unknown,
Their life left for others.
We play at God with our necromancy,
but forces far more potent
sleep within these stones.
<size:31>{Brutus' first innovation as Lord Incarcerator was a weighted chain around every neck so that his prisoners would forever bow to him.}
<size:30>{"Let us not forget the most important lesson the Vaal taught us:
Nothing is eternal."
- Siosa Foaga, Imperial Scholar}
Primed, curved and sleek.
Decisive and final.
For malice and righteousness.
There's but one solution.
The line between having not enough to do and too much to do is unusually fine.
Upon silent paws and masked by the reeds,
Farrul's hunt begins as the light recedes.
No blade subdues vice;
Guide offenders to virtue,
Unveil their lost sight.
The village elders had a curious rule: If you hear three voices scream for aid, flee as fast as you can.
A ruler is only as powerful as he is wealthy.
Control the coin, control the empire.
"Oh no, I couldn't possibly afford this fine artefact. I'm... just looking."
<size:28>{Crimson rubies, drops of vigour,
flowing through my veins,
flesh like coal, try to crush me,
diamond is what remains.}
Try a thousand times, and eventually you'll have to give up.
I've never come upon a ship I could not command. I have however met sailors that were not willing to be led.
They said they were here to protect us.
Eternal beauty has a cost, one which Shavronne was happy to pay with the lives of others.
<size:31>{It's always easier to find your way if you draw a map of the progress you've made.}
Even the brightest eventually fade to darkness.
The academic route to knowledge is wide and well-trodden; but it is the untaught one who scales the mountain.
The swarm began with just a couple of children. Now, it is her entire existence.
Beware the sudden calm, for it is a sure sign of a storm on the horizon.
<size:25>{Summoned for the King's desire,
soon applause came from the court.
However insanity was his only sire,
so the King's reign was cut short.}
<size:29>{"I swore to use my position to help the people. What good is power when it just accumulates on the already-powerful?" - Erasmus, Imperial Gemcutter}
<size:28>{We live to dream of worlds we aren't in,
a false narrative that we use to fill our souls
with doubt;
The world is already beautiful,
there's no need to dream.}
<size:28>{First, I gave my wealth, and we went hungry. Next, I gave my land, and we were homeless. Then, I gave my family, and I was alone. Last, I gave my eyes, and all I could dream was mine.}
"In the forest again... But at least I have these."
"I'm going for a walk. I'll be back soon."
- Blonca's last words
Even the most learned man is a fool to his own fate.
A taste of power brings a hunger for more.
Our Lady Dialla,
as a symbol of our progress,
shines greater than all the gems.
<size:29>{A mind as quick as lightning,
fists as hard as stone,
a heart that burns with fury,
and eyes that chill to the bone.}
"The Karui was correct; there is virtue in honouring my ancestors."
To tame a beast, you first must subdue its heart.
The strongest emerge from suffering. The toughest bear the most scars. The sole survivor claims the greatest of rewards.
Discovery can lead to beauty, or it can lead to ruin.
<size:23>{Vintage or crafted, Glittering and shiny
Dusty or glittering, huge or tiny
Secured within a chest
or unearthed from your mining
Find jewellery everywhere,
no need for divining!
So why is it so hard
to figure out which one to wear?
This one makes me stronger,
but does it match my hair?}
The pain you feel is of no consequence, it is evolution, to be made whole within something greater.
"The process of eternal youth is a give and take. You give them death and take their youth."
- Zerphi of the Vaal
When sky meets ground the flames can be found, but who has the will to tame them.
Bound by fate,
inseparable by choice.
Though the years weakened his mind, his body remained deadly as ever.
<size:31>{500 times Kaom's axe fell, 500 times Kaom's Heart splintered. Finally, all that remained was a terrible, heartless Fury.}
In the hands of a master craftsman, a worthless pebble can adorn the crown of a king.
"Our rulers are being ridiculous, and we are suffering."
In the pursuit of wealth, as in that of power, anything goes.
"Don't worry, I know what I'm doing."
- Toggo's Last Words
In a world filled with chaos, he could always seek comfort in the hands of his master.
Wherever she went, death was sure to follow.
Greed is a hunger that only grows as you feed it
<size:25>{They thought winter had come early,
that snow blanketed the land,
but in truth, all their chickens
had come home to roost.}
When the world burned, the greedy burned with it, while the clever left as paupers.
Formless might,
Wild beauty tamed,
The brine of gods,
The seas restrained.
"Forge me a carapace from their skin, imbued with their soul. Then feed their flesh to the hounds."
Some powers are far too great even for the
gods of old.
They stand among us, and within us.
When the darkness weighs upon you, grow light from within.
You gave us life and love, more than you could spare. Now you're gone, and we are stranded, alone, cold and without purpose.
<size:28>{You can't seek riches without getting your hands dirty.}
Time cannot wash away that which cannot be forgotten.
You'll never know the things you miss if you keep your eyes closed
<size:31>{As their civilisation crumbled, the Vaal looked to their queen. In her, they saw a way out. In them, she saw a burden she was happy to free herself from.}
A dream from which you cannot awake is nothing other than a nightmare.
<size:34>{He dispels dark realms
until mortal sufferings
yield to hopeful light.}
"More! I want more!" - Faendris, the Insatiable
An oath once made is an oath never broken. Do not delay in keeping it, for I take no pleasure in fools.
<size:28>{I thought love stronger than all,
but time and isolation broke
that which madness could not.}
<size:31>{Publicly, he lived a pious and chaste life of poverty. Privately, tithes and tributes made him and his lascivious company very comfortable indeed.}
To cure the Goddess,
and break the chains of corruption,
you must shatter the world.
<size:26>{At the beck and call
of The Siren's hand,
winter ravages
the trembling land,
and the weight of ice that binds
will break the strongest of minds.}
<size:27>{God had forsaken the land
And Victario wept.
Corruption consumed the land
And Victario's tears turned to blood.}
<size:28>{"For all your struggles, all your achievements, even for the greatest of us, a story is all that remains. Write it well."
-Julius Perandus, Father of Chitus}
With staff in hand
and wrath in heart,
your soul and corpse
shall surely part.
"There is no right or wrong choice, no best or worst. There are only choices and their consequences."
Every obsession began with a single, innocent taste.
<size:29>{Shrieking souls locked away
Hate splits frozen cells asunder
The knot of corruption
undone at last}
<size:29>{"Fate was always my nemesis...
But it didn't stop me then, and it won't stop me now."
- Kjetilbrann, The Undaunted}
<size:25>{Cede all power and wealth to me and serve me in perpetuity.
A minor inconvenience I assure you.}
A beacon on the horizon; a guiding light, a call for help, or a warning to turn back.
<size:30>{Many strive for greatness,
but it is challenge, unforseen,
that forges heroes.}
The howls and cackling could not mask the sadness.
"Paint, metal, flesh... A true artist does not limit himself." - Malachai the Soulless
If you beckon the
Lord of Lightning,
do not be surprised
when you are struck.
<size:30>{A King Loved By All,
A Shadow Awaiting Nightfall,
A Speaker Howling Away,
A Hunter Seeking Prey}
<size:26>{Embrace death to honour the lost,
no fear in life no matter the cost.
With one of all we are,
and all of one we trust,
throughout past, present and future... be just.}
<size:28>{Every skull was once a person.
Though 'Who?' is rarely asked.
Friends, who wear
the crown of Nook,
Never need to ask.
They remember.}
Wrapped in the glory of the heavens, she comes to mete out justice for the fallen.
"This was the proudest moment of my life."
"... so far"
Turn the crank,
close your eyes,
and pray to the gods
for a pleasant surprise.
